    public class GeographicPosition
extends PropertyBase<java.lang.String,GeographicPosition>

    GEO Geographic Position RFC 5545 iCalendar 3.8.1.6. page 86

    This property specifies information related to the global position for the activity specified by a calendar component.

    This property value specifies latitude and longitude, in that order (i.e., "LAT LON" ordering).

    Example: GEO:37.386013;-122.082932

    See Also:
    VEvent, VTodo
